'''"Bliss ninny"''' is a pejorative term for a person who is unrealistically optimistic, or a [[Pollyanna]] and who might seem to prefer to retreat from a difficult reality by professing seemingly irrelevant platitudes, rather than to directly engage with the difficulty at hand in a meaningful way.  This word is popularly used on the Internet to describe Internet chat-room participants who, according to [http://redwing.hutman.net/%7Emreed/warriorshtm/blissninny.htm Flame Warrior] will often attempt to interrupt a heated discussion by attempting to interject "vacuous comments.... about (their cats)."  According to the [http://www.rickross.com/reference/rainbow/rainbow16.html Rick Ross] website, within the [[Rainbow Tribe]] the term refers to "a Rainbow (Tribe member) who spends most of his or her time stoned on marijuana."  This term is also sometimes used by students of [[A Course in Miracles]] to refer to a Course student who may seem to have become "overly intoxicated with", but "underly grounded in" Course principles.

